de.coderarea.jrdp.protocol.TS

Enum TsClientSecurityData.TsEncryptionMethods

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<TsClientSecurityData.TsEncryptionMethods>
      • de.coderarea.jrdp.protocol.TS.TsClientSecurityData.TsEncryptionMethods
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<TsClientSecurityData.TsEncryptionMethods>
    Enclosing class:
    TsClientSecurityData

    public static enum TsClientSecurityData.TsEncryptionMethods
extends Enum<TsClientSecurityData.TsEncryptionMethods>
    A 32-bit unsigned integer. Cryptographic encryption methods supported by the client and used in conjunction with Standard RDP Security. The client MUST specify at least one encryption method, and the server MUST select one of the methods specified by the client.

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      ENCRYPTION_FLAG_128BIT
      128-bit session keys MUST be used to encrypt data (with RC4) and generate MACs.
      ENCRYPTION_FLAG_40BIT
      40-bit session keys MUST be used to encrypt data (with RC4) and generate Message Authentication Codes (MAC).
      ENCRYPTION_FLAG_56BIT
      56-bit session keys MUST be used to encrypt data (with RC4) and generate MACs.
      ENCRYPTION_FLAG_FIPS
      All encryption and Message Authentication Code generation routines MUST be Federal Information Processing Standard (FIPS) 140-1 compliant.
